{"action": "edit", "code": "def get_row_with_highest_non_black_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, this function returns the row with the highest number of non-black pixels.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    An integer representing the row with the highest number of non-black pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    row_sum = np.sum(input_grid != black, axis=1)\n    return np.argmax(row_sum)\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    r = get_row_with_highest_non_black_pixels(input_grid)\n    out = replace_black_pixels(input_grid, r)\n    c = get_column_with_highest_non_black_pixels(input_grid)\n    out = replace_black_pixels_in_column(out, c)\n    return out\ndef replace_black_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray, row: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    All non-black pixels in row r of the input_grid are continuous. The black pixels on the left are replaced from left to right in order of non-black pixels from left to right, while the black pixels on the right are replaced from right to left in order of non-black pixels from right to left. If the number of black pixels to be replaced is greater than that of non-black pixels, cycle through the replacement in the above order.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    row: An integer representing the row number.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the modified grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_black_pixels = np.where(input_grid[row] != black)[0]\n    num_non_black_pixels = len(non_black_pixels)\n    black_pixels = np.where(input_grid[row] == black)[0]\n    num_black_pixels = len(black_pixels)\n    if num_black_pixels == 0:\n        return input_grid\n    for i in range(num_black_pixels):\n        if i < num_non_black_pixels:\n            input_grid[row][black_pixels[i]] = input_grid[row][non_black_pixels[i]]\n        else:\n            input_grid[row][black_pixels[i]] = inpu